CWEs: CWE-78: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an OS Command ('OS Command Injection')
description: The function unique_name_285 is vulnerable to command injection. This is because it uses user-supplied input (pathBundleIN.cert, pathBundleIN.key, pathBundleIN.ca, pathOUT, password) in a command that is executed by the system. An attacker could potentially inject malicious commands by providing specially crafted input.
